From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: GE-Proton <git@localhost>
Date: Tue, 21 Jul 2026 16:35:00 -0600
Subject: [PATCH] mmdevapi: Mimic a Sony speaker replug after hotplug settles.

Spider-Man Remastered can observe the fresh Sony controller speaker
endpoint after a controller model switch, but still keep routing its
controller-effect stream to the normal render default until the same
controller is physically unplugged and plugged back in.  A delayed add
notification and stale collection refresh make the new endpoint visible,
but they do not always drive the game's endpoint cache through the same
remove/add path as a real replug.

On the second delayed settle pass, synthesize a remove notification for
the still-current Sony controller speaker, wait briefly, verify that the
same endpoint is still present, then re-send the add/state notification.
Do not also re-signal the normal render default on this synthetic replug:
the first settle pass already does that, and nudging the game back toward
the default render endpoint after the controller speaker replug can make
Spider-Man keep effect audio on the main output until the controller is
physically replugged again.

This keeps the stricter disconnect semantics intact: real disconnects
still delete and forget the old controller endpoint, and the delayed
notification only targets the fresh endpoint that is still active in the
live device list.

---
 dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c | 12 +++++++++---
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
index ad42f26f701..7fdfc4325b1 100644
--- a/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
+++ b/dlls/mmdevapi/devenum.c
@@ -1005,8 +1005,16 @@ static DWORD WINAPI delayed_endpoint_notification_thread(void *arg)
             if (!endpoint_notification_is_current_dualsense_mono(&delayed->notifications[i]))
                 continue;
 
-            TRACE("Delayed re-signaling DualSense mono endpoint add %s after hotplug settled, pass %u.\n",
-                    debugstr_guid(&delayed->notifications[i].guid), pass + 1);
+            TRACE("Delayed re-signaling Sony mono endpoint %s %s after hotplug settled, pass %u.\n",
+                    pass ? "replug" : "add", debugstr_guid(&delayed->notifications[i].guid), pass + 1);
+
+            if (pass)
+            {
+                notify_endpoint_removed(delayed->notifications[i].flow, &delayed->notifications[i].guid);
+                Sleep(50);
+                if (!endpoint_notification_is_current_dualsense_mono(&delayed->notifications[i]))
+                    continue;
+            }
             notify_endpoint_added_state(delayed->notifications[i].flow, &delayed->notifications[i].guid,
                     delayed->notifications[i].state);
             signaled = TRUE;
@@ -1016,7 +1024,7 @@ static DWORD WINAPI delayed_endpoint_notification_thread(void *arg)
             signaled = TRUE;
         }
 
-        if (signaled)
+        if (signaled && !pass)
             notify_current_render_default_device_changed();
     }
 
